     5	/// Slot index assigned to a running task invocation.
     6	///
     7	/// The engine allocates one slot per concurrent agent/program and releases the
     8	/// slot when the invocation exits. The renderer uses the slot to update the
     9	/// correct tile without reconciling task ids on every frame. The type is
    10	/// wider than a byte so callers with very large `--parallel` values cannot
    11	/// silently collide into slot 255.
